node.title: Victoria records 1,268 new local COVID cases and seven deaths
node.alt: Healthcare workers in full PPE look on as other workers speak to people at car windows at a drive-through vaccination site.

node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,268\u00a0new local COVID-19 cases and seven\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 16,662\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 352\u00a0people have died during the current Delta outbreak.", "There are 651\u00a0people in hospital in Victoria with COVID-19, of whom 106\u00a0are in intensive care, and 70\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The new cases were detected from 65,410\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 15,058\u00a0doses of vaccine given at state-run centres yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
